# Task accuracy — evidence-first standard (all work)

Applies to **every** task: Cloudflare, Supabase, app UI, Mastra, CopilotKit, CI, docs, booking, planner, commerce — not Cloudflare-only.

Companion skills: `task-verifier` (Done gate), `lean` (lifecycle), `ponytail` (smallest change), domain hubs (`ipix-supabase`, `cloudflare`, …).

## Principles

- Verify before changing.
- Evidence over assumptions — never guess.
- One concern per task / PR / commit.
- Preserve architecture consistency.
- Prevent documentation drift.
- Align with Linear, PRDs, and `origin/main`.
- If unverifiable → write **NOT VERIFIED**.
- Do not reopen completed work or re-recommend already-fixed issues.
- Mitigations are not complete fixes — label them honestly.

## Stage 1 — Scope

Before code:

1. Compare with `origin/main`.
2. Check overlapping PRs / branches.
3. Read related Linear issue + AC.
4. Classify: ✅ In scope · ⚠️ Related but separate · ❌ Out of scope.

Do not expand scope. File a new Linear issue for out-of-scope root causes.

## Stage 2 — Evidence

For every finding / review comment, collect from:

1. Current source (`rg`, graphify, file read)
2. Installed package / types when API shape disputed
3. Official docs (MCP when available)
4. Runtime reproduction when possible

Classify: ✅ Confirmed · 🟡 Unproven · ⚪ Already fixed · ❌ Incorrect · ⚠️ Out of scope.

**Only implement confirmed, in-scope issues.**

## Stage 3 — Implementation

- One logical change at a time; small commits.
- Prefer reuse / extend (ponytail ladder).
- No drive-by refactors.
- Stop and open Linear if the real fix belongs to another epic.

## Stage 4 — Testing

Focused first (unit / typecheck / lint on touched paths), then broader suite / build as required by lean mode and path verify matrix.

## Stage 5 — Verification level (required label)

| Level | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| Unit Verified | Tests only |
| Build Verified | App / Worker builds |
| Local Runtime Verified | Local server / `wrangler dev` / linked DB probe |
| Remote Preview Verified | Preview deploy / remote non-prod |
| Production Verified | Live production evidence |

Never claim production readiness without Production Verified evidence.

## Stage 6 — Docs / Linear sync

Before Done: contradiction check — implementation matches docs, AC, counts, commands, links. No aspirational checkboxes.

## Stage 7 — Architecture

No duplicate SSOT, clear ownership, no unnecessary abstractions, domain skill best practices.

## Stage 8 — Merge / Done gate

CI green · review threads resolved · security/RLS when applicable · regression tests when behavior changed · docs updated · remaining risks named.

Use `@task-verifier` before Linear Done on IPI tasks.

## Reporting (after each stage or at handoff)

| Item | Result |
|------|--------|
| Finding | Exact issue |
| Evidence | Code / Docs / Runtime / MCP |
| Classification | Confirmed / Unproven / Already Fixed / Incorrect / Out of Scope |
| Change Made | Files (or none) |
| Regression Test | Added / updated / N/A |
| Validation Level | Unit / Build / Local Runtime / Remote Preview / Production |
| Scope Preserved | Yes / No |
| Remaining Risks | Details |
| Next Action | Details |

## Quality gates (all applicable must pass)

- [ ] Current architecture / `origin/main` checked
- [ ] Scope preserved
- [ ] Verification level stated honestly
- [ ] Docs + Linear synchronized
- [ ] No unresolved contradictions
- [ ] No duplicate implementations
- [ ] Production readiness evaluated (or explicitly not claimed)
